#' Calculate Copy Number Alterations (CNA) from Fragment Count Data
#'
#' @description
#' This script calculates copy number alterations (CNA) from fragment count data
#' processed through QDNAseq. It is specifically designed for DELFI data downloaded
#' from FinaleDB. The script takes fragment counts in predefined genomic bins,
#' applies QDNAseq filtering and normalization, and outputs copy number log2-ratios
#' in BED format.
#'
#' @details
#' The workflow consists of the following steps:
#' 1. Read fragment count file (generated by bedtools intersect)
#' 2. Generate QDNAseq read count object with binned fragment data
#' 3. Apply QDNAseq filtering (residual and blacklist)
#' 4. Estimate and correct for technical biases
#' 5. Normalize bins and smooth outliers
#' 6. Segment bins and call copy number gains/losses
#' 7. Format and save results as BED file
#'
#' @usage
#' Rscript calculate_CNA_from_frag.R -i <count_file> -b <bin_file> -o <output_dir>
#'
#' @arguments
#' \describe{
#'   \item{-i, --input}{Character. Path to input count file containing fragment counts
#'     per bin (output from: bedtools intersect -b fragments.bed -a bins.bed -c)}
#'   \item{-b, --bin}{Character. Path to QDNAseq bin file in RDS format
#'     (e.g., bin100kb.rds or bin1M.rds)}
#'   \item{-o, --output}{Character. Directory path where output BED file will be saved}
#' }
#'
#' @output
#' A BED-format file with columns: chromosome, start, end, log2.ratio
#' File naming: <sample_name>.<bin_name>.bed
#'
#' @dependencies
#' QDNAseq, Biobase, dplyr, tidyverse, GenomicRanges, BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19,
#' hash, Rsamtools, parallel, argparse, testit, comprehenr
#'
#' @author
#' Trong Hieu Nguyen
#'
#' @note
#' - Input count file must be pre-generated using: 
#'   bedtools intersect -b /path/to/frag/file -a /path/to/bin/file -c
#' - This script is optimized for DELFI datasets from FinaleDB
#' - Requires reference genome BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19 (hg19 coordinates)
# ***** note *****
# this script is specially applied to DELFI data downloaded from FinaleDB!!!

gc()
